    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA286-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai melinta talaimakaḷait tōḻi vaṟpuṟuttatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante encouraged HER who has become weak in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA286">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            ūca loṇkuḻai yuṭaiviyat taṉṉa</l>
<l>            vattak kumiḻi ṉāyita ḻalari</l>
<l>            kallaṟai varikkum pulleṉ kuṉṟañ</l>
<l>            ceṉṟōr maṉṟa celīiyareṉ ṉuyireṉap</l>
<l>            puṉaiyiḻai nekiḻa vimmi nontunon </l>
<l>            tiṉaita lāṉṟici ṉāyiḻai niṉaiyi</l>
<l>            ṉaṭṭō rākkam vēṇṭiyu moṭṭiya</l>
<l>            niṉṟō ḷaṇipeṟa varaṟku</l>
<l>            maṉṟō tōḻiyavar ceṉṟa tiṟamē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O [you] of choice jewels, leave off despairing,</l>
<l rend="indent">aching [and] aching, sobbing for [your] adorning jewels to become loose,</l>
<l rend="indent">saying “may my life go: he has gone indeed</l>
<l rend="indent2">to the empty hills, where the choice petals of the Kumiḻ tree</l>
<l rend="indent2">by the road adorn(?) the stony rocks,</l>
<l rend="indent3">like an expanse with swinging bright earrings.”</l>
<l>If [you] think, is not the reason he has gone, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">[his] needing gain for those who are near [to him]</l>
<l rend="indent">and coming so that your shoulder that has shrunk obtains adornment?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
